---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Interactive" description="Live mathematical visualizations powered by Pretext">
  <h1>Interactive Mathematics</h1>
  <p class="page-intro">
    Live visualizations of our computational results. Text layout powered by
    <a href="https://github.com/chenglou/pretext">Pretext</a> —
    measuring and flowing text without DOM reflows.
  </p>

  <section class="manifesto" id="manifesto-section">
    <div id="manifesto-stage"></div>
    <div class="manifesto-orb" id="manifesto-orb"></div>
  </section>

  <script type="module">
  import { prepareWithSegments, layoutNextLine } from '/js/pretext.js';

  const stage = document.getElementById('manifesto-stage');
  const orbEl = document.getElementById('manifesto-orb');
  const section = document.getElementById('manifesto-section');
  if (!stage || !orbEl || !section) throw new Error('missing elements');

  const TEXT = `Why Human–AI Collaboration Changes Everything\n\nConsider how mathematical progress has always worked. A human is born somewhere on Earth. They survive childhood. Somehow, through an improbable chain of circumstances — the right school, the right teacher, the right book left open on the right page — they discover they have a talent for abstract thought. They spend decades training. If they're extraordinarily lucky, they produce a handful of results that push a field forward by the time they're forty or fifty. Then they slow down, and the world waits for the next one.\n\nWe waited 200 years between Euler and Ramanujan. A century between Gauss and Grothendieck. The entire edifice of modern mathematics — every theorem, every conjecture, every computational technique — rests on the output of a few thousand people across all of human history who happened to be born, happened to survive, happened to find mathematics, and happened to be productive during their brief window of peak creativity.\n\nThis is an absurd way to advance knowledge.\n\nThe bottleneck was never the mathematics itself. The bottleneck was always biological: waiting for nature to randomly assemble a mind capable of seeing what others couldn't. The proofs were always there. The patterns were always there. The continued fraction identities, the spectral gaps, the Kronecker coefficients — they existed before anyone computed them. We just had to wait for the right human to come along and look.\n\nHuman–AI collaboration breaks this cycle. Not because AI replaces human insight — it doesn't. The deep intuition that says "this conjecture should be true" or "this approach will never work" remains fundamentally human. What AI does is eliminate the waiting. A mathematician with AI collaboration can explore computational landscapes that would take a lifetime to traverse alone. They can test conjectures across billions of cases in minutes. They can write, debug, and optimize GPU kernels for problems they conceived that morning. The time between "I wonder if..." and "here is the data" collapses from years to hours.\n\nEvery result on this site was produced this way. A human directed the research — chose the conjectures, judged the approaches, decided what mattered. AI agents wrote CUDA kernels, constructed proofs, generated documentation, and managed the computational pipeline. Neither could have produced these results alone. The human without the AI would still be hand-checking continued fractions. The AI without the human would have no idea which continued fractions to check.\n\nThe 27 exceptions to Zaremba's conjecture with A={1,2,3}. The 26.4 billion Kronecker coefficients for S₃₀. The 30 billion class numbers of real quadratic fields. The complete Hausdorff dimension spectrum for a million continued fraction Cantor sets. None of these existed in the literature before this project. Not because the mathematics was too hard — but because no single human lifetime had enough hours to compute them, and the traditional system had no mechanism to accelerate the process.\n\nWe cannot afford to keep waiting for nature to randomly produce the next Euler. The open problems are too important, the tools are too powerful, and the data is too vast. Human–AI collaboration is not a shortcut or a crutch. It is the only honest response to the fact that mathematics is infinite and human lifetimes are not.\n\n— Cahlen Humphreys, 2026. Built with Claude.`;

  const FONT = '16px/1.75 "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", "Book Antiqua", Palatino, Georgia, serif';
  const LINE_HEIGHT = 28;
  const ORB_RADIUS = 80;
  const PAD = 40;

  let orbX = 300, orbY = 200;
  let targetX = 300, targetY = 200;
  let prepared = null;
  let lines = [];

  async function init() {
    prepared = prepareWithSegments(TEXT, FONT, { whiteSpace: 'pre-wrap' });
    reflow();

    section.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
      const r = section.getBoundingClientRect();
      targetX = e.clientX - r.left;
      targetY = e.clientY - r.top;
    });

    requestAnimationFrame(animate);
  }

  function reflow() {
    const W = section.clientWidth - PAD * 2;
    stage.innerHTML = '';
    lines = [];

    let cursor = { value: 0 };
    let y = PAD;
    let lineIdx = 0;

    while (cursor.value < TEXT.length && y < 5000) {
      // Check if orb overlaps this line band
      const lineTop = y;
      const lineBot = y + LINE_HEIGHT;
      let availWidth = W;
      let offsetX = 0;

      // Circle-line intersection: does the orb overlap [lineTop, lineBot]?
      const orbCenterY = orbY;
      const orbCenterX = orbX - PAD;
      const dy = Math.max(lineTop - orbCenterY, 0, orbCenterY - lineBot);

      if (dy < ORB_RADIUS) {
        // Orb overlaps this line — compute horizontal exclusion
        const dx = Math.sqrt(ORB_RADIUS * ORB_RADIUS - dy * dy);
        const orbLeft = orbCenterX - dx;
        const orbRight = orbCenterX + dx;

        // Text goes on the wider side
        if (orbLeft > W - orbRight) {
          // More space on the left
          availWidth = Math.max(orbLeft - 10, 50);
          offsetX = 0;
        } else {
          // More space on the right
          availWidth = Math.max(W - orbRight - 10, 50);
          offsetX = orbRight + 10;
        }
      }

      const result = layoutNextLine(prepared, cursor, availWidth);
      if (!result) break;

      const lineEl = document.createElement('div');
      lineEl.className = 'mline';
      lineEl.textContent = result.text;
      lineEl.style.top = y + 'px';
      lineEl.style.left = (PAD + offsetX) + 'px';
      lineEl.style.width = availWidth + 'px';

      // Style the title line
      if (lineIdx === 0) {
        lineEl.style.fontSize = '22px';
        lineEl.style.fontWeight = 'bold';
        lineEl.style.color = '#e8c47a';
      }

      stage.appendChild(lineEl);
      lines.push(lineEl);

      cursor = result.cursor;
      y += LINE_HEIGHT;
      lineIdx++;
    }

    section.style.height = (y + PAD) + 'px';
  }

  function animate() {
    // Smooth follow
    orbX += (targetX - orbX) * 0.08;
    orbY += (targetY - orbY) * 0.08;

    orbEl.style.left = (orbX - ORB_RADIUS) + 'px';
    orbEl.style.top = (orbY - ORB_RADIUS) + 'px';

    // Only reflow if orb moved enough
    if (Math.abs(orbX - lastReflowX) > 3 || Math.abs(orbY - lastReflowY) > 3) {
      reflow();
      lastReflowX = orbX;
      lastReflowY = orbY;
    }

    requestAnimationFrame(animate);
  }

  let lastReflowX = 0, lastReflowY = 0;
  init();
  </script>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Zaremba Witness Distribution</h2>
    <p>
      Drag the slider to explore how the witness ratio α(d)/d concentrates
      around 0.171 as d grows. Each bubble is a value of d, sized by its
      CF length, colored by max partial quotient.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-witness-golden-ratio/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/zaremba-conjecture-verification/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="witness-viz">
      <canvas id="witness-canvas"></canvas>
      <div class="viz-controls">
        <label>
          <span>Max d:</span>
          <input type="range" id="witness-max-d" min="100" max="10000" value="1000" step="100">
          <span id="witness-d-label" class="mono">1000</span>
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Spectral Gap Landscape</h2>
    <p>
      The congruence spectral gaps σ<sub>m</sub> for all 1,214 square-free moduli
      up to m=1999. Hover over any point to see the modulus, factorization,
      and gap value. The red dashed line marks the Bourgain-Kontorovich threshold.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-spectral-gaps-uniform/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/zaremba-transfer-operator/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="spectral-viz">
      <canvas id="spectral-canvas"></canvas>
      <div id="spectral-tooltip" class="tooltip"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>CF Tree Explorer</h2>
    <p>
      The continued fraction tree with partial quotients in &#123;1, &hellip;, 5&#125;.
      Each path from root to leaf gives a Zaremba denominator. Watch the
      tree grow and see how quickly it covers the integers.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-conjecture-proved/">Finding →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="tree-viz">
      <canvas id="tree-canvas"></canvas>
      <div class="viz-controls">
        <label>
          <span>Depth:</span>
          <input type="range" id="tree-depth" min="1" max="9" value="5">
          <span id="tree-depth-label" class="mono">6</span>
        </label>
        <button id="tree-animate" class="viz-btn">Animate Growth</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Zaremba Density Phase Transition</h2>
    <p>
      For digit set A, the Zaremba density measures what fraction of integers d have a
      coprime a/d with all CF partial quotients in A. A sharp phase transition occurs
      between A=&#123;1,2&#125; (58%) and A=&#123;1,2,3&#125; (99.997%). The transition is controlled
      by the Hausdorff dimension crossing 1/2.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-density-phase-transition/">Finding →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="density-viz">
      <canvas id="density-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Class Number Distribution</h2>
    <p>
      Distribution of class numbers h(d) for 2.74 billion real quadratic fields
      Q(√d) with d&nbsp;∈&nbsp;[10<sup>9</sup>,&nbsp;10<sup>10</sup>). Dominated by powers of 2
      (genus theory). The Cohen-Lenstra prediction of 75% with h=1 is far from realized
      at this scale — convergence is non-monotone.
      <a href="/findings/class-number-convergence/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/class-numbers-real-quadratic/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="classnum-viz">
      <canvas id="classnum-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Hausdorff Dimension Spectrum</h2>
    <p>
      Hausdorff dimension dim<sub>H</sub>(E<sub>A</sub>) for every subset
      A&nbsp;⊆&nbsp;&#123;1,…,10&#125;, grouped by cardinality |A|. Each dot is one of
      the 1,023 nonempty subsets. Adding digit 1 has the largest effect on
      dimension — 5 digits including 1 beat 9 digits without it.
      <a href="/findings/hausdorff-digit-one-dominance/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/hausdorff-dimension-spectrum/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="hausdorff-viz">
      <canvas id="hausdorff-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .page-intro {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-style: italic;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    .page-intro a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--accent); }

    .manifesto {
      position: relative;
      margin-bottom: 4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--surface);
      min-height: 600px;
      cursor: default;
    }
    #manifesto-stage {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
    }
    #manifesto-stage .mline {
      position: absolute;
      white-space: pre;
      font: 16px/1.75 "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", "Book Antiqua", Palatino, Georgia, serif;
      color: var(--ink-secondary);
      user-select: text;
      transition: left 0.15s ease, width 0.15s ease;
    }
    .manifesto-orb {
      position: absolute;
      width: 160px;
      height: 160px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at 40% 35%,
        rgba(232,196,122,0.15) 0%,
        rgba(232,196,122,0.06) 40%,
        rgba(232,196,122,0.02) 70%,
        transparent 100%);
      border: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.12);
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 2;
      box-shadow:
        0 0 40px rgba(232,196,122,0.05),
        inset 0 0 30px rgba(232,196,122,0.03);
    }
    .manifesto-orb::after {
      content: '\u03C6';
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      font: 36px "Iowan Old Style", Georgia, serif;
      color: rgba(232,196,122,0.25);
    }
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .manifesto { min-height: 400px; }
      .manifesto-orb { display: none; }
    }

    .interactive-section {
      margin-bottom: 4rem;
    }
    .interactive-section h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .interactive-section p {
      color: var(--ink-secondary);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .viz-container {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    canvas {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .viz-controls {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      align-items: center;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .viz-controls label {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .viz-controls input[type="range"] {
      width: 200px;
      accent-color: var(--accent);
    }

    .mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.82rem; }

    .viz-btn {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--accent);
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 30%, transparent);
      padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 160ms ease;
    }
    .viz-btn:hover { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent); }

    .tooltip {
      display: none;
      position: absolute;
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--ink);
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 10;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
  </style>

  <div id="load-interactive"></div>
</Base>
